356
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,740
Wait, why are there three packs of tissues
with one box of yogurt?

357
00:22:30,870 --> 00:22:32,740
I don't know.
It was like this when I got it.

358
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:35,080
You fetched them on purpose,
didn't you?

359
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,790
You should put them back.

360
00:22:37,370 --> 00:22:38,790
Just two packs of tissues?

361
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:40,290
Do you think we stole them?

362
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:42,250
- Mom...
- Be quiet.

363
00:22:42,410 --> 00:22:43,580
I didn't say that.

364
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:46,200
One pack of yogurt,
one pack of tissues for free.

365
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,620
But there are three packs.

366
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:49,040
I have a reason to suspect you.

367
00:22:49,620 --> 00:22:50,660
What do you mean?

368
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,740
Where's your manager?

369
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:53,170
What are you talking about?

370
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:54,740
Why are you yelling at me?

371
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:55,740
If you feel wronged,

372
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:56,740
let's check the surveillance

373
00:22:56,740 --> 00:22:58,160
and see what really happened.

374
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,080
What?

375
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:03,160
Deng Shasha.

376
00:23:03,370 --> 00:23:05,040
Is this your mom?

377
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:07,540
Why is she arguing with the clerk?

378
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:09,960
Shasha.

379
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:11,120
Is she your classmate?

380
00:23:11,580 --> 00:23:12,990
Girl, listen,

381
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,410
don't buy anything here.

382
00:23:14,450 --> 00:23:15,790
They're so stingy!

383
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,200
Watch your attitude!

384
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:18,240
I'll file a complaint!

385
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,240
What's the big deal?

386
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,370
I'm not buying them!

387
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:23,490
Don't drag me. Get off me!

388
00:23:24,790 --> 00:23:26,700
We did make a mistake.

389
00:23:26,830 --> 00:23:28,450
Hurry. It's so embarrassing!

390
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,700
Embarrassing?

391
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,080
I told you to put them in your pocket,

392
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,660
but you didn't listen to me.

393
00:23:32,740 --> 00:23:34,580
I'm embarrassing? Then find another mom!

394
00:23:45,450 --> 00:23:46,290
Mom!

395
00:23:46,580 --> 00:23:48,830
My classmate saw what happened.

396
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:50,410
She loves gossiping.

397
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:51,740
How am I supposed to face them?

398
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:53,620
Can you stop trying to get freebies?

399
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:54,950
Do you think I'm embarrassing?

400
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:57,330
Why am I always thrifty?

401
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:58,540
I'm doing this for our family!

402
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:00,880
They say

403
00:24:01,450 --> 00:24:03,450
a child is never
ashamed of their family.

404
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,290
You're so ungrateful

405
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:06,490
just like your useless dad!

406
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,200
You're always saying this.

407
00:24:11,870 --> 00:24:13,870
But you've saved money for Deng Peng

408
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:15,620
so that he can buy an apartment!

409
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:18,240
You've always been stingy with me!

410
00:24:18,950 --> 00:24:20,330
How could you blame me?

411
00:24:20,410 --> 00:24:21,620
Stealing is wrong!

412
00:24:23,790 --> 00:24:25,200
My years of sacrifice meant nothing!

413
00:24:26,330 --> 00:24:27,200
If I had known this,

414
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:28,950
I shouldn't have had you!

415
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:33,240
Then why did you have me?

416
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,490
I've ended up like this
all because of you.

417
00:24:37,990 --> 00:24:38,830
You taught me

418
00:24:38,870 --> 00:24:40,620
to flatter those rich people

419
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:43,330
and get freebies.

420
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,660
What kind of mother are you?

421
00:24:50,290 --> 00:24:51,660
You're ashamed of me, right?

422
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,490
Then don't call me Mom!

423
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:00,790
Shasha!

424
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,290
Why are you here?

425
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:08,080
Where are you going?

426
00:26:08,290 --> 00:26:09,490
It's late at night.

427
00:26:09,490 --> 00:26:10,740
What if you get kidnapped

428
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:11,950
and sold to the mountains?

429
00:26:12,370 --> 00:26:13,210
So what?

430
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:15,080
Life goes on wherever you are.

431
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:18,580
What are you doing here at this hour?

432
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:21,450
Your mom told us what happened.

433
00:26:21,740 --> 00:26:23,410
We've been looking for you.

434
00:26:24,950 --> 00:26:26,950
Now you've found me.

435
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,160
Mission accomplished.

436
00:26:28,370 --> 00:26:29,290
You can go.

437
00:26:31,580 --> 00:26:32,450
We've been looking for you.

438
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:34,580
At least let us take a break.

439
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:35,710
Here.

440
00:26:36,370 --> 00:26:37,210
Sit down.

441
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:42,200
Shasha,

442
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,370
I know how deeply this has hurt you.

443
00:26:44,950 --> 00:26:46,950
But didn't we tell you the other day?

444
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:49,330
Whenever you feel upset,

445
00:26:49,330 --> 00:26:50,450
you can talk to us.

446
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:53,330
No matter what,
we're still best friends.

447
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:56,160
I'm fine.

448
00:26:57,830 --> 00:27:00,370
Shasha, stop acting strong.

449
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:02,290
You said it was fine,

450
00:27:02,450 --> 00:27:03,950
but you've been alone all day.

451
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:04,950
You didn't come to us.

452
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,990
So, you're still angry.

453
00:27:07,410 --> 00:27:08,250
However, that's

454
00:27:08,410 --> 00:27:09,540
how misunderstandings work.

455
00:27:09,910 --> 00:27:10,950
The more you care,

456
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,330
the more badly you get hurt.

457
00:27:12,740 --> 00:27:14,200
We care about each other,

458
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:15,540
so

459
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:17,700
why don't we forget about our grudges,

460
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,540
get to know each other,

461
00:27:19,830 --> 00:27:20,950
and become friends again, okay?

462
00:27:21,950 --> 00:27:22,790
Shasha.

463
00:27:23,580 --> 00:27:24,950
Just give me another chance.

464
00:27:25,450 --> 00:27:26,580
We'll start over, okay?

465
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:27,540
I promise,

466
00:27:27,660 --> 00:27:28,500
I won't

467
00:27:28,660 --> 00:27:30,080
suspect you again.

468
00:27:30,510 --> 00:27:31,430
I'll be

469
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:32,620
at your service, okay?

470
00:27:34,990 --> 00:27:35,830
Shasha,

471
00:27:35,910 --> 00:27:37,370
could you please forgive me?

472
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:39,450
Can we go back to the old days?

473
00:27:41,990 --> 00:27:44,700
I've told you I'm not angry at you.

474
00:27:46,490 --> 00:27:47,410
I'm just

475
00:27:48,990 --> 00:27:51,120
angry at my mom.

476
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:54,950
She thinks your families

477
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,040
are richer

478
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,370
than mine.

479
00:27:57,910 --> 00:27:58,750
She thinks

480
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:00,700
you'll be useful to me.

481
00:28:00,990 --> 00:28:03,490
So, she told me to flatter you

482
00:28:03,540 --> 00:28:04,990
and get close to you.

483
00:28:05,410 --> 00:28:06,700
However, I really want

484
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:08,240
to be your true friend.

485
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,040
But when I think about what she said,

486
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,490
I realize I'm doing exactly

487
00:28:12,490 --> 00:28:13,990
what she told me to do.

488
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,410
It's not true.

489
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:19,910
Niannian, I made friends with you

490
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,700
not because of your family.

491
00:28:22,410 --> 00:28:23,250
I know.

492
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:24,910
I know what kind of person you are.

493
00:28:26,450 --> 00:28:28,240
So, I argued with her this time.

494
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:30,990
Why is my mother like this?

495
00:28:35,330 --> 00:28:36,170
Shasha,

496
00:28:36,410 --> 00:28:39,200
maybe your mom did make some mistakes,

497
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:41,330
but she still loves you.

498
00:28:41,580 --> 00:28:43,790
She just expressed it in the wrong way.

499
00:28:44,290 --> 00:28:45,790
You can try to understand her.

500
00:28:47,870 --> 00:28:48,710
She even

501
00:28:48,870 --> 00:28:51,040
wanted to steal a pack of tissues.

502
00:28:51,660 --> 00:28:53,080
Everyone was watching us.

503
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:54,580
It was so embarrassing!

504
00:28:54,910 --> 00:28:56,160
How should I understand her?

505
00:28:56,330 --> 00:28:57,540
Do I have to become

506
00:28:57,540 --> 00:28:58,910
someone like her?

507
00:28:59,490 --> 00:29:00,330
Shasha,

508
00:29:00,950 --> 00:29:01,950
have you ever thought about

509
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:03,120
why she'd do that?

510
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:04,950
She wants to save money

511
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,200
for more important things.

512
00:29:07,790 --> 00:29:09,370
She's been saving money

513
00:29:09,660 --> 00:29:10,660
so that you can afford

514
00:29:10,660 --> 00:29:12,450
clothes and food,

515
00:29:13,830 --> 00:29:15,790
and Deng Peng
can have money to get married.

516
00:29:15,830 --> 00:29:17,160
She's not doing this for me.

517
00:29:17,290 --> 00:29:19,120
I'm a girl, so she never

518
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,540
really cares about me.

519
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,200
To be honest,

520
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,540
your family does prefer boys.

521
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:27,700
My mom also has a bad temper.

522
00:29:27,830 --> 00:29:29,740
She's always dressed up properly,

523
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:30,910
but when she gets angry,

524
00:29:30,910 --> 00:29:31,990
she's completely different.

525
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:33,290
It's terrifying.

526
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,080
Every parent

527
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,790
